/*
    Negative — referencing an unknown variant on `builtin`'s Os enum
    fires the enum-variant-miss diag. Uses qualified access on the
    enum TYPE (`builtin.Os.no_such_os`) so the lookup is independent
    of the host — Path A's implicit dead-arm elimination would
    otherwise let the bad variant slip through in a switch arm.

    Expected diag (1):
    - no variant 'no_such_os'
*/

builtin :: @import("builtin")

bad :: builtin.Os.no_such_os
